===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{senseid|en|gathering of yarn etc}} A quantity of [[yarn]], [[thread]], or the like, put up together, after it is taken from the [[reel]]. A skein of cotton yarn is formed by eighty turns of the thread around a fifty-four inch reel.
#* '''1935''', {{w|T.S. Eliot}}, ''{{w|Murder in the Cathedral}}'', Part I:
#*: You  hold the '''skein''': wind, Thomas, wind
#*: The thread of eternal life and death.
# {{lb|en|figuratively}} A [[web]], a [[weave]], a [[tangle]].
#* '''1923''', {{w|Arthur Conan Doyle}}, "{{w|The Adventure of the Creeping Man}}"
#*: The practical application of what I have said is very close to the problem which I am investigating. It is a tangled '''skein''', you understand, and I am looking for a loose end.
# {{lb|en|zoology}} The [[membrane]] of a [[fish]] [[ovary]].
# {{qualifier|wagonmaking}} A metallic strengthening band or [[thimble]] on the wooden arm of an axle.
#: {{rfquotek|en|Knight}}
# {{lb|en|zoology|provincial England}} A group of wild [[fowl]], (e.g. [[goose|geese]], [[gosling]]s) when they are in [[flight]].
# {{lb|en|sports}} A [[winning streak]].

